WEEK 7 ANSWERS
7. Cultural Diversity and Globalization:
Globalization has brought societies closer together, facilitating the exchange of ideas, goods, and information on an unprecedented scale. While this connectivity offers many benefits, it also raises questions about the preservation of cultural diversity. As local traditions and languages encounter external influences, efforts to protect and celebrate cultural heritage become vital. Finding ways to promote intercultural understanding and mutual respect in an increasingly interconnected world is a complex endeavor.
